%% Data Flow Diagram - odh-model-controller
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / kubectl
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Controller as odh-model-controller<br/>(Manager)
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant NGCAPI as NVIDIA NGC API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Gateway as Envoy Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Authorino as Authorino<br/>TLS (EnvoyFilter)

    Note over User,Authorino: Flow 1: InferenceService Deployment (RawDeployment Mode)
    User->>K8sAPI: POST InferenceService CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutate/Validate InferenceService<br/>TLS client auth
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch event (InferenceService)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create OpenShift Route<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceMonitor/PodMonitor<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ClusterRoleBinding<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create KEDA TriggerAuthentication<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Note right of Controller: Route: TLS Edge or Reencrypt

    Note over User,Authorino: Flow 2: LLMInferenceService Authentication Setup
    User->>K8sAPI: POST LLMInferenceService CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch event (LLMInferenceService)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Gateway AuthPolicy<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute AuthPolicy<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Istio EnvoyFilter<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Note right of Controller: EnvoyFilter configures<br/>TLS to Authorino

    Note over User,Authorino: Flow 3: NIM Account Reconciliation
    User->>K8sAPI: POST NIM Account + API key Secret<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate NIM Account<br/>TLS client auth
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch event (NIM Account)
    Controller->>NGCAPI: Validate API key<br/>Auth: API Key (Bearer)
    NGCAPI-->>Controller: Model catalog response
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap (model list)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Pull Secret (NGC)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create OpenShift Templates<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount

    Note over User,Authorino: Flow 4: Multi-Node Ray TLS Certificate Setup
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Pod CREATE (multi-node SR)<br/>TLS client auth
    Webhook->>Webhook: Inject Ray TLS init-container<br/>& volume mounts
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Pod spec
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch event (Pod started)
    Controller->>Controller: Generate per-pod TLS cert<br/>signed by ray-ca-tls CA
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update ray-tls Secret<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Note right of Controller: Init-container reads cert<br/>from volume mount

    Note over User,Authorino: Runtime: External Client Request
    User->>Router: GET/POST model endpoint<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    Router->>K8sAPI: Route to Predictor Service<br/>80/443 TCP
    User->>Gateway: Request to LLMInferenceService<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>Authorino: Auth check<br/>TLS (via EnvoyFilter)
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth decision
